SPA Alembic migrations — BL-008 Phase 3

Backend selection lives in env.py and is driven by the same env var the
rest of the app uses: SPA_DATABASE_URL.

  unset                        -> spa_core/database/spa.db  (SQLite)
  sqlite:///path.db            -> SQLite at that path
  postgresql://user:pw@host/db -> PostgreSQL via psycopg2

CLI cheat sheet (run from spa_core/database/):

  alembic upgrade head                 # apply all pending migrations
  alembic downgrade -1                 # revert one migration
  alembic current                      # show currently applied revision
  alembic history                      # list all revisions
  alembic upgrade head --sql > out.sql # offline mode: emit SQL only

Override the URL per-invocation without exporting an env var:

  alembic -x url=postgresql://user:pw@localhost/spa upgrade head

The cutover procedure for production is documented in
docs/postgres_cutover.md.
